                      "general_quantity_modifier": "REL",
                      "quantity_236": "TER,FY/DE"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " Energy spectra of H-isotopes in ternary fission."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Analysis the spectra of fast pile neutron and",
                " fission neutrons from the sample are expected to be",
                " similar, and the spectra of protons from (np)",
                " reactions induced by pile and fission neutrons are",
                " also to be similar. So in the final result for",
                " proton, the background was multiplied by a constant",
                " factor before subtracting. this factor, 2.0 +-.0.2,",
                " was defined as the ratio of the background due to",
                " all neutrons to the background due to epicadmium",
                " neutrons from the pile. All the spectra are",
                " sufficiently well fitted by a Gaussian distribution."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
